The paper deals with geometric variants of the set cover problem, which is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). It also discusses the capacitated set cover problem, which is a well-studied problem in operations research and computer science, and involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) as well as combinatorial optimization (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions approximation algorithms, which are a common topic in theoretical computer science and optimization (cs.IT).
